Liang Chenye is now working in Huawei open source team, focus on container related technologies. Before join Huawei, he worked at SUSE as a China R&D manager, responsible for maintaining/developing SUSE Linux Enterprise products and taking part in choosing a new technology as a candidate commercial product.  

Chenye has over ten years open source experience, very active in open source communities, like GNOME, openSUSE. Not only takes part in project development but he also helps to promote these communities by building their ASIA community as well. As a co-founder, he founded an open source alliance “Kai yuan she” in China which now have over 50 members including Microsoft, Canonical and Firefox. 

Chenye has been involved in contributing to OCI community since August 2015. He joins the discussion of OCI specification in mailing list and weekly meeting and participates in the OCI tool development. As the OCI testing owner, he creates the OCI Testing project to verify the compliance of different runtimes. The testing project keeps update with OCI spec and sends the feedback to OCI community. 

With strong enthusiasm and community ability, Chenye will strive to expand the OCI influence, and of course reflect and adhere to OCI values.



